Harry G. SEABOLDT v. PENNSYLVANIA RAILROAD COMPANY v. THOMPSON MAHOGANY COMPANY, Third-Party Defendant, Appellant. No. 14269. United States Court of Appeals Third Circuit. Argued May 23, 1963. Decided May 31, 1963. See also 290 F.2d 296. Lynn L. Detweiler, Philadelphia, Pa. (Swartz, Campbell & Henry, Philadelphia, Pa., on the brief), for appellant. F. Hastings Griffin, Jr., Philadelphia, Pa. (William J. Sharkey, Dechert, Price & Rhoads, Philadelphia, Pa., on the brief), for appellee.

Before KALODNER, STALEY and SMITH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On review of the record we find no error. The District Court’s Order and Judgment dated October 26, 1962 will be affirmed.
